Title : Portal:Hong Kong/Did you know/4
Text : <div style="float:right;margin-left:0.5em;">
[[File:Law Uk Folk Museum.jpg|100x100px|right|Law Uk Folk Museum]]
</div>
*... that Hong Kong's '''[[Law Uk Folk Museum|Law Uk]]''' ''(pictured)'' is the sole surviving village house and the last example of traditional [[Hakka people|Hakka]] housing in [[Chai Wan]], a former Hakka village?
*... that '''[[Madame Tussauds Hong Kong]]''' is the oldest permanent [[wax museum]] in [[Asia]]?
*... that the '''[[Causeway Bay Typhoon Shelter]]''' was the first of its kind in [[Hong Kong]]?
*... that '''[[Sakai Takashi]]''', a General of the [[Imperial Japanese Army]] during [[World War II]], was [[capital punishment|sentenced to death]] on [[August 27]], [[1946]] for [[crimes against humanity|atrocities]] committed against civilians and surrendered soldiers in [[Hong Kong]]?
*... that '''[[Millennium City, Hong Kong]]''' has [[skyscraper]]s numbered 1, 2, 3, and 5, possibly because 4 is considered [[luck|unlucky]]?
